** About Us **

Listed on the New York Stock Exchange, Civeo is a leading global provider of
workforce accommodation solutions. Civeo Australia has over 9,000 permanent
rooms under management in Queensland, New South Wales and Western Australia.
In addition, Civeo Australia also operates approximately 9,000 rooms in
client-owned properties in remote regions of Western Australia.

** Your Role **

As the Senior Business Analyst, Property Systems you will be entrusted with
leading the analysis and design of complex business systems and processes.
Leveraging your expertise, you'll collaborate closely with stakeholders from
various departments to identify opportunities for improvement, define
requirements and recommend innovative solutions.

Your ability to utilise use case analysis and effectively define and document
business requirements, will be essential in driving the success of projects.
Furthermore, your demonstrated expertise in business process modeling, IT
project management and translating business requirements into functional and
technical specifications will play a crucial role in ensuring the alignment of
solutions with organisational objectives.

Additionally, your strong skills in eliciting and documenting user
requirements, analysing requirements, testing, and suggesting process
improvements will be vital in driving continuous enhancement and innovation.

** About You **

You will have a post-secondary degree or Diploma in Computer Science,
Business, IT, or related field. With a minimum 3+ yearsâ€™ experience in systems
analysis, preferably with JD Edwards or Hospitality systems, you will possess
strong knowledge of technical business process analysis, system development
life cycle process, and proficiency in workflow, process design, reporting,
and data analysis.

Familiarity with hospitality systems like Oracle Simphony and Kiosk systems
will be highly regarded, along with experience in supporting Property
Management Systems and ERP applications such as, Oracle JD Edwards.

** Working at Civeo **

Civeo offers a range of great benefits to its employees, including:

  * Flexible work arrangements. 
  * Education Assistance Policy and Employee Assistance Program; and 
  * Corporate discounts and rewards and salary sacrifice options for superannuation. 

Civeo is a proud supporter of mutually beneficial partnerships within our
communities, which is why we connect with Traditional Owners and First Nations
Businesses, leading the way in sustainable partnerships. Aboriginal & Torres
Strait Islander applicants are strongly encouraged to apply.

